<HEADLINE>
<P>
CBS SUSPENDS ANDY ROONEY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CBS was totally correct in its timely response to the remarks attributed to 
Rooney if for no other reason than to solidify its policy of condemning those 
who preach hate and promote bigotry without concern about the consequences or 
having to answer for their actions. 
</P>
<P>
Although I am African American and have had my share of prejudicial experiences 
resulting from the biased attitudes that are so prevalent in our society, I am 
unable to disagree entirely with the remarks by Rooney. Yet, realizing how 
deep-rooted the practices are to draw conclusions that all African American 
people fall into the category of school dropouts, pregnant, drug users, I have 
no choice but to consider such demeaning comments as insulting racial slurs and 
agree that CBS took the proper action and set an example that others need to 
follow. 
</P>
<P>
JOHN ViDAHL 
</P>
<P>
Windsor Hills 
</P>
