<P>
PROTEST DISRUPTS BUSH'S SPEECH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I have known and admired Mary Brent Wehrli for many years, and have seen her 
transition from a comfortable middle-class life of caring wife and mother, 
including involvement in church and community activities, to that of an 
impassioned, committed Christian. At some point, she decided to cross the line 
between caring and total commitment, including the possibility of facing 
ostracism, indignity and even danger. How much we need to be aroused from our 
self-satisfied, self-serving complacency by those who remind us of a higher 
moral purpose. 
</P>
<P>
NANCY WEAVER DURKA 
