<HEADLINE>
<P>
DAMEWORTH RUNS 4:13.1 IN TIMES GAMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bryan Dameworth lost a race for the first time in nearly a year, but it took a 
field full of Olympians to do it Friday in the Times/Eagle Indoor Games at the 
Forum. 
</P>
<P>
Dameworth, an Agoura High senior, finished ninth in the men's Open Mile despite 
running a lifetime best of 4 minutes 13.1 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
But that time was nearly 18 seconds slower than winner Peter Elliott. The 
two-time British Olympian ran 3:55.51 to beat Algerian Nourredine Morcelli, 
running for Riverside Junior College. 
</P>
<P>
Dameworth's previous best was 4:14.4, run last summer at UCLA. He ran 4:14.52 
two weeks ago in winning a featured high school mile in Millrose Games at 
Madison Square Garden in New York City. 
</P>
</TEXT>
