<P>
HARVARD BREAKS 100 IN ROUT OF BLAIR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Harvard High's fast-break offense operated on all cylinders Friday night as the 
Saracens routed Blair, 109-78, in a Southern Section 3-A Division basketball 
playoff game. 
</P>
<P>
The win at the Harvard gym pushed the Saracens' winning streak to 15 games and 
moved Harvard into Tuesday's quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
Matt Clark scored 12 of his 25 points in the first quarter as the Saracens 
raced to a 33-17 lead. Harvard (22-2) increased its lead to 62-37 at halftime 
and 90-55 after three quarters. 
</P>
<P>
Harvard senior guard Rick Osterloh led all scorers with 30 points and center 
Andres Carlo added 15. 
</P>
<P>
For Blair (7-17), reserve Mike Gray scored 22 points and James King added 18. 
</P>
