Notre Dame 99, Moorpark 74 -- Leading 13-8 in the first quarter, Notre Dame 
scored 24 unanswered points and turned the 3-A Division game at Notre Dame into 
a rout. 
</P>
<P>
Notre Dame's G. C. Marcaccini made four three-point shots in the first quarter 
and finished with a game-high 24 points. 
</P>
<P>
Bob DaCorsi added 22 for Notre Dame, and Steve Colella had 15 points and 11 
rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Robert Hernandez led Moorpark with 18 points. Both teams are 14-10. 
</P>
<P>
In Tuesday's quarterfinals, the the Knights meet Rancho Alamitos, an 86-58 
winner over South Pasadena. 
</P>
<P>
Chaminade 63, Beaumont 62 -- Junior Kent Cote (16 points) sank a pair of free 
throws with nine seconds to play to give visiting Chaminade (14-10) a 63-59 
lead in a 2-AA Division game. Beaumont (13-10) hit a three-point shot with a 
second to play. 
</P>
<P>
Chaminade's Mark Mirkovich tossed in a game-high 18 points and Colin Havert 
handed out seven assists. Mark Wiltshire had 10 rebounds for Chaminade, which 
moves to Tuesday's quarterfinals against Santa Clara, a 60-50 winner over Pius 
X. 
</P>
<P>
Montclair Prep 83, Rosamond 53 -- Jack Shemtov scored 20 points and Chris 
Sanger added 14 points and 10 rebounds for host Montclair Prep (19-4) in a 1-A 
Division game. 
</P>
<P>
Cardell Henderson had 10 points and 10 rebounds and Ed Cibrian scored 15 points 
for Montclair Prep, which plays Faith Baptist in the quarterfinals Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Faith Baptist 77, Flintridge Prep 70 -- Alex Estrada had 27 points and 10 
assists and Peter Rasmussen added 18 points and 14 rebounds for host Faith 
Baptist (16-10) in a 1-A Division game. 
</P>
<P>
Fernando Garcia scored 14 points, Darren Wyre had 12, and Robert Reed grabbed 
10 rebounds for Faith Baptist. 
</P>
