<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROSE TO DO DAILY RADIO COMMENTARY IN CINCINNATI 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CINCINNATI 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pete Rose has agreed to do daily baseball commentary for a radio station -- his 
first media venture since his lifetime banishment from baseball. 
</P>
<P>
The former Cincinnati Red manager will do three-minute daily commentaries and a 
once-a-week interview with a sports broadcaster on WCKY-AM in Cincinnati. 
</P>
<P>
The station said the features are scheduled to begin March 19 and continue 
through the World Series. 
</P>
<P>
Rose was banned from baseball last August after admitting he bet with 
bookmakers. While he was manager, Rose did daily interviews on the Reds' radio 
network. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
ROSE, PETE; NEWSCASTERS; BASEBALL; RADIO BROADCASTS 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
