</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: NAMES IN THE NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Joe Walton, fired after seven years as the New York Jets' coach, was hired as 
the Pittsburgh Steelers' offensive coordinator. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
COACHES; PITTSBURGH STEELERS (FOOTBALL TEAM); WALTON, JOE 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA021790-0070 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 177672 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
February 17, 1990, Saturday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 8; Column 2; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
94 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dennis (Oil Can) Boyd, who signed with Montreal this winter after eight years 
with Boston, accused Boston Manager Joe Morgan and some of his former Red Sox 
teammates of racist attitudes. 
</P>
<P>
"All I wanted was for Morgan to treat me with respect. Morgan was bad for me. . 
. . He felt blacks couldn't pitch. He felt they couldn't think out there on the 
mound." 
</P>
<P>
Morgan denied the allegations. 
</P>
<P>
"I have no idea where he's coming from and I don't really care to comment on 
it," Morgan said. "I'm not upset because it's not true, but I'm not too happy, 
either." 
</P>
</TEXT>
