<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two teen-agers were arrested in connection with the fatal shooting of a 
35-year-old man in Logan Heights early Friday, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Two officers were on patrol at 2 a.m. in the 3600 block of Main Street when 
witnesses told them a man had been shot in a nearby Vesta Street duplex, police 
spokesman Dave Cohen said. 
</P>
<P>
The witnesses directed police to two teen-agers near Vesta and Dalbergia 
streets, where a 15- and a 17-year-old were arrested. One of the boys had a 
.22-caliber revolver, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim was found in a back bedroom of the residence in the 2000 block of 
Vesta Street, with a gunshot wound in his upper body, police said. He died an 
hour later at UC San Diego Medical Center. His identity was being withheld 
pending notification of relatives. 
</P>
