</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION BASKETBALL PLAYOFFS; 
</P>
<P>
4-A BOYS; 
</P>
<P>
BISHOP MONTGOMERY HOLDS OFF BUENA PARK RALLY FOR 59-51 WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVID RAATZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Buena Park cut a 19-point deficit in the first half to two, but still lost to 
Bishop Montgomery, 59-51, Friday night in the second round of the Southern 
Section 4-A playoffs at Bishop Montgomery. 
</P>
<P>
The Coyotes (12-13) were led by sophomore center Gavin Molinar's 16 points. 
</P>
<P>
Darrell Daniel had eight points in a 13-0 run that gave Bishop Montgomery 
(16-7) a 20-7 lead at the end of the first quarter. Daniel finished with 22. 
</P>
<P>
Buena Park, which got 13 points from Ray Lanier, missed all nine of its 
free-throw attempts in the second quarter and trailed by 15 at halftime and by 
10 going into the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
But the Coyotes scored the first six points of the fourth quarter to cut their 
deficit to 44-38. 
</P>
<P>
Two free throws by Donyell Collins -- who was held to four points, six below 
his average -- brought Buena Park to 46-44 with 4:11 to play. 
</P>
<P>
A three-point basket by Kirk Jones 40 seconds later gave Bishop Montgomery a 
five-point lead, and the Coyotes never got closer than that down the stretch. 
DAVID RAATZ 
</P>
