<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE WOMEN'S BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
JACKSON SCORES 40 TO LEAD GOLDEN WEST PAST FULLERTON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Forward Claudette Jackson scored 40 points to lead the Golden West College 
women's basketball team to a 110-80 victory over Fullerton in the Orange Empire 
Conference women's basketball regular-season final Friday at Golden West. 
</P>
<P>
Donna Gondringer added 36 for Golden West, the top-ranked team in the state, 
which won its 12th in a row. 
</P>
<P>
Golden West (31-1, 12-0) led, 54-42, at the half. 
</P>
<P>
In other Orange Empire Conference women's games: 
</P>
<P>
Orange Coast 95, Saddleback 54 -- Kami Bigler scored 21 points and had seven 
rebounds as Orange Coast set a single-season record for victories. Cindy Kollar 
added 18 points and 10 rebounds for OCC (26-5, 10-2). Shannon Garnos scored 16 
points for Saddleback (13-16, 4-8). 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Santiago 56, Cypress 30 -- Sophomore center Carolyn Burns scored 23 
points and had 17 points to lead Rancho Santiago (8-15, 3-9). Charisse Simon 
had 12 points and Barbara Olson had 11 for Rancho Santiago. Tami Bartley scored 
16 points for Cypress (0-26, 0-12). 
</P>
</TEXT>
