<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASKETBALL ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Avocado League 
</P>
<P>
El Camino 91, Carlsbad 61 -- Travis Gilley scored 18 points and Dee Boyer added 
16 for El Camino (18-6, 11-1). El Camino tied with San Pasqual for the league 
title. Mark Tague scored 17 points for Carlsbad (8-14, 5-7). 
</P>
<P>
San Pasqual 80, Ramona 62 -- Erik Meek led San Pasqual (17-5, 11-1) with 26 
points and 15 rebounds. Bryan Benner added 18 points and eight rebounds. San 
Pasqual led 42-23 at halftime. Alfonso De La Nuez scored 16 points for Ramona 
(15-7, 6-6). 
</P>
<P>
Oceanside 64, San Marcos 47 -- Owen Dennis scored 14 points and had five 
rebounds for Oceanside (13-12, 6-6). D.J. Lewis added 12 points and 10 
rebounds. Oceanside led in every quarter. San Marcos finished 1-21, 0-12. 
</P>
<P>
Palomar League 
</P>
<P>
Torrey Pines 69, Fallbrook 60 -- The victory gave No. 4 Torrey Pines a share of 
the league title with Mt. Carmel. The Falcons have now won or shared three 
consecutive league titles. Bill Scheibe had 18 points and Chris Stevens added 
16 for Torrey Pines (24-3, 12-2). Chris Miller had 32 for Fallbrook (16-10, 
7-7). 
</P>
<P>
Mt. Carmel 124, Vista 65 -- Mt. Carmel rebounded from its loss to Rancho Buena 
Vista Tuesday with the rout. The victory gave Mt. Carmel a share of the league 
title with Torrey Pines. Mt. Carmel (20-4, 12-2) out-rebounded Vista, 66-28. 
Vista was just 2 of 32 from three-point range. Shane Knight had 29 points and 
16 rebounds for Mt. Carmel. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Buena Vista 76, Poway 65 -- The teams were tied after the third quarter 
but RBV outscored Poway, 22-11, in the fourth. Darryl Parker scored 36 points 
and had 19 rebounds for RBV (15-9, 10-4). Poway is 17-6, 8-6. 
</P>
<P>
City Eastern League 
</P>
<P>
Serra 66, Morse 48 -- Roderick Alexander scored 19 points and Desi Dixon added 
17 as Serra (7-13, 1-7) got its first league victory. 
</P>
<P>
City Harbor League 
</P>
<P>
Coronado 59, Marian 40 -- James Stark scored 15 and Derek Wastila and Adam 
Smith added 13 apiece to give Coronado the league title. Coronado (16-9, 6-2) 
outscored Marian (8-14, 1-7), 18-8, in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Clairemont 80, Christian 67 -- Clairemont trailed by three at the end of the 
third quarter but outscored Christian 30-12 in the fourth quarter. Alex Love 
scored 34 points and had 13 rebounds for Clairemont (7-14, 3-5). Tony Clark 
scored 46 points for Christian (12-11, 5-3). 
</P>
<P>
City Western League 
</P>
<P>
Kearny 82, La Jolla 61 -- Darnay Scott scored 28 points and Mike Oviedo added 
17 for Kearny (16-10, 4-4). Lupe Estrada scored 12 for La Jolla (4-18, 1-7). 
</P>
<P>
USDHS 55, Mission Bay 41 -- USDHS outscored Mission Bay, 16-5, in the third 
quarter on its way to the victory at Mission Bay (4-16, 2-6). Peter Ellis 
scored 12 to lead USDHS (20-3, 7-1). 
</P>
<P>
City Central League 
</P>
<P>
Madison 76, Hoover 64 -- John McKenna scored 21 points and Kirk Cumming added 
16 for Madison (3-22, 1-8). John Akridge led Hoover (5-18, 1-7) with 18 points. 
</P>
<P>
Coastal League 
</P>
<P>
Bishop's 58, Parker 54 -- Brian Allbers scored 28 points and had 11 rebounds to 
lead Bishop's (21-4, 12-0) to a league title. 
</P>
