<P>
HIGH PESTICIDE LEVELS FOUND INSIDE HOMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pesticides may travel long distances through the air and become trapped in 
homes years after they were applied, a study issued in Washington by the 
Environmental Protection Agency suggested. Monitoring of 259 homes in 
Jacksonville, Fla., and Springfield, Mass., for 32 substances used in farming 
and consumer products found the indoor levels of some chemicals to be 50 to 90 
times greater than the levels outdoors. The consumer products included bug 
sprays, disinfectants and termite chemicals. 
