<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHERIFF ILLEGALLY SEIZES ARMORY TO HOUSE INMATES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SPRINGFIELD, Mass. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fed up with months of overcrowding in the county jail, a sheriff on Friday 
commandeered a National Guard armory as a temporary prison. 
</P>
<P>
Hampden County Sheriff Michael Ashe said that he took the action "to prevent 
the collapse of the criminal justice system. . . . " 
</P>
<P>
State Secretary of Public Safety Charles V. Barry said Ashe had been notified 
it was illegal to put prisoners in the armory. He was ordered to have them 
removed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
