<HEADLINE>
<P>
4.1 QUAKE RATTLES SAN BERNARDINO COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A mild earthquake jolted parts of San Bernardino County on Friday night, but no 
damage or injuries were reported. 
</P>
<P>
The temblor, which struck at 7:45 p.m., registered magnitude 4.1, officials at 
the state Office of Emergency Services said. 
</P>
<P>
The epicenter was about six miles northwest of Lake Arrowhead. 
</P>
<P>
Dispatchers at the San Bernardino County Sheriff's Department said they did not 
feel the tremor. Many area residents also did not notice the quake. 
</P>
<P>
"I didn't even feel it," said Debby Chormicle, a clerk at a 7-Eleven store at 
Crestline. "It didn't shake anything off the shelves." 
</P>
</TEXT>
