<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAN ACCUSED OF STEALING ARTIFACTS FOR HOME CHAPEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COVENTRY, R.I. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A "deeply religious" man was charged Friday with keeping thousands of dollars 
worth of artifacts stolen from area churches in a "chapel" in his home where he 
apparently conducted his own services, police said. 
</P>
<P>
William Silva, 22, of Coventry surrendered at the town police station. Some of 
the items included vestments, gold-lined chalices, crucifixes, a bronzed 
coffin, mortuary equipment, church kneelers, Latin prayer plaques and a crimson 
skullcap. 
</P>
</TEXT>
